    {
      "id": "596747533521424",
      "score": 3,
      "review_title": "It's a start, not much fun",
      "review_description": "There are few things I didn't like but the idea is great.\nHolding a tool feels like a wobbly effect, holding a crowbar doesn't feel right or any tool for that matter\nHitting with the pointing side of crowbar doesn't produces realistic deformation of the clay which means all the tools have same deformation zones and doesn't matter which tools one uses.\nI got bored pretty quick.\nBasically the only thing this game should provide is the unique and precise deformation physique of the clay being hit. Until this is life-like it won't be as entertaining. \nVoice is same for all the clay statues, or I didn't find a way to change that. Female statue or animals same male voice that repeats after four to five sentences.\nIdea is great but it needs more love from devs for sure. Thanks for giving us the chance to test.",
      "date": 1742069239,
      "review_helpful_count": 12,
      "author_display_name": "coudys",
      "author_alias": "coudys",
      "developer_response": {
        "body": "Hi coudys, just to let you know we took your feedback on board and dropped an update to improve the realism of the weapons and to modify so each does different levels and types of impact (like the crowbar).\n\nWe also added an economy based around smashing the faces to match a target to get cash to unlock weapons, as well as a punch power meter. \n\nIf you get a chance to play again, we'd love to hear what you think of the changes? Thank you",
        "date": 1742661785
      }
